vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
  colors: {
    purple: "#8B5CF6"
    blue: "#3B82F6"
    blue-light: "#DBEAFE"
    green: "#10B981"
    green-light: "#D1FAE5"
    orange: "#F97316"
    orange-light: "#FED7AA"
    red: "#EF4444"
    red-light: "#FEE2E2"
    gray: "#6B7280"
    gray-light: "#F3F4F6"
  }
}
title: Merkle Tree Difference Detection {
  near: top-center
  shape: text
  style: {
    font-size: 28
    bold: true
    underline: true
  }
}
Step 1: Compare Root Hashes {
  style.fill: ${colors.blue-light}
  style.stroke: ${colors.blue}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  |'md
**Compare Root Hashes**
- Node A: `hash_abcd = 0x7f3a...`
- Node B: `hash_abcd = 0xb2c1...`
- **Result**: Hashes differ → proceed to Step 2
  '|
}
Step 2: Identify Differing Subtree {
  style.fill: ${colors.orange-light}
  style.stroke: ${colors.orange}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  |'md
**Compare Child Hashes**
- Left subtree: A=`0x1a2b`, B=`0x1a2b` ✓ (match)
- **Right subtree: A=`0x3c4d`, B=`0x9e8f` ✗** (differ)
- **Result**: Recurse into right subtree
  '|
}
Step 3: Recurse to Leaves {
  style.fill: ${colors.green-light}
  style.stroke: ${colors.green}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  |'md
**Compare Right Subtree Leaves**
- Key "c": A=v3, B=v3 ✓
- **Key "d": A=v4, B=v7 ✗**
- **Result**: Identify differing key "d"
  '|
}
After: List of Differing Keys {
  style.fill: ${colors.purple}
  style.fill-pattern: lines
  style.stroke: ${colors.purple}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.font-color: white
  |'md
**Differing Keys Found**

["d"]  // A has v4, B has v7

Node with higher version wins via LWW
  '|
}
Step 1 -> Step 2: "Roots differ" {
  style.stroke: ${colors.blue}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.bold: true
}
Step 2 -> Step 3: "Right subtree differs" {
  style.stroke: ${colors.orange}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.bold: true
}
Step 3 -> After: "Leaf comparison complete" {
  style.stroke: ${colors.green}
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.bold: true
}